% Automatisch generiert — Thema: Abortion
% arg/1 Fakten
arg(pro29).  % [pro] The World Health Organization estimated in 2004 that unsafe abortions cause 68,000 maternal deaths worldwide each year.
arg(pro29b).  % [pro] Many of the maternal deaths occur in developing countries where safe and legal abortion services are difficult to access.
arg(pro7).  % [pro] If the State is interested in protecting fetal life after viability, the State may go so far as to prescribe abortion during the period after viability, except when it is necessary to preserve the life or health of the mother.
arg(pro71).  % [pro] Americans are more accepting of abortions that occur early in pregnancy when the fetus is not as developed and is not “viable” (able to survive on its own outside of the woman’s body).
arg(pro63).  % [pro] According to this argument, not all abortions are unjustified.
arg(pro63b).  % [pro] Abortion would be justified if the same justification could be applied to killing an adult human.
arg(pro58).  % [pro] Abortion reduces crime.
arg(pro36).  % [pro] The National Cancer Institute (NCI), the American Cancer Society (ACS), and the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists all refuted the claim that abortion can lead to a higher probability of developing breast cancer.
arg(con140).  % [con] Susan B. Anthony and Elizabeth Cady Stanton led the fight for women's right to own property, to vote, and to obtain equal education.
arg(con140b).  % [con] Susan B. Anthony and Elizabeth Cady Stanton spoke out against abortion.
arg(con23).  % [con] I will always support legislation that would end abortion or lead us in the direction of ending abortion.
arg(con152).  % [con] For this reason, I introduced S. 583, the Life at Conception Act on March 14, 2013.
arg(con109).  % [con] Half of all women having abortions each year have had at least one previous abortion, according to the Guttmacher Institute.
arg(con109b).  % [con] In 2010, 8.5 % of abortions reported to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention were performed on women who had three or more previous abortions.
arg(con9).  % [con] Abortion is not permissible from the point at which individual human identity is realized.
arg(con8).  % [con] Fetuses feel pain during the abortion procedure.

% att/2 Fakten  (Dung 1995 — binär; Typ/conf aus LLM-Kandidaten als Kommentar)
att(pro29b, con23).  % [undermining] conf=70 — A shows that ending abortion would likely raise maternal deaths, challenging B's aim to end abortion.
att(pro29b, con152).  % [undermining] conf=75 — A provides evidence that lack of safe abortion increases deaths, undermining B's justification for the Life at Conception Act.
att(con9, pro7).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — Con9’s claim that abortion is never permissible directly conflicts with pro7’s allowance for abortion regulation after viability.
att(con9, pro71).  % [undermining] conf=70 — The claim that abortion is impermissible from the point of human identity challenges the premise that viability determines acceptability.
att(con8, pro71).  % [undermining] conf=80 — Stating that fetuses feel pain attacks the premise that early, less‑developed fetuses make early abortions more acceptable.
att(con140b, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=75 — Claiming that early feminists opposed abortion contradicts the conclusion that some abortions are justified.
att(con23, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — A pledge to end abortion asserts all abortions are unjustified, directly opposing the claim that some are justified.
att(con152, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — Introducing legislation defining life at conception implies abortion is unjustified, rebutting the claim that some abortions are justified.
att(con9, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — Con9 asserts abortion is never permissible, directly contradicting pro63's claim that some abortions are justified.
att(con23, pro63b).  % [rebuttal] conf=85 — Con23’s commitment to ending abortion directly opposes pro63b’s claim that abortion is justified.
att(con152, pro63b).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — Con152’s legislative effort to ban abortion contradicts pro63b’s justification of abortion.
att(pro63b, con9).  % [rebuttal] conf=95 — Con9 declares abortion impermissible, directly contradicting pro63b's claim that abortion is justified.
att(con23, pro58).  % [rebuttal] conf=70 — Con23 advocates ending abortion, contradicting pro58's claim that abortion is beneficial (reduces crime).
att(con152, pro58).  % [rebuttal] conf=70 — Con152 promotes legislation to restrict abortion, opposing pro58's assertion that abortion reduces crime.
att(con9, pro58).  % [undermining] conf=70 — Con9 attacks the premise that abortion can be freely performed, which pro58 relies on to claim it reduces crime.
